n sozialen Medien sowie die Erfahrungen von Betroffenen analysiert. Damit werden Einblicke in die aktuelle Forschung ermöglicht, die auch engagierte Bürger_innen adressiert.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4a2018. 4aAlltagsrassismus. 4aAntisemitismus. 4aChemnitz. 4aCultural Studies. 4aFraming. 4aKultur. 4aKulturtheorie. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aRadikalisierung. 4aRechtsextremismus. 4aRechtsradikalismus. 4aSoziale Medien. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aCultural Theory.  aRacism.  aRight-wing Extremism.1 aAsbrock, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorlett, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriese, Heidrun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriese, Heidrun, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHoffmann, Felix, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaiser, Vera, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKooroshy, Shadi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMecheril, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNolden, Marcus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNolden, Marcus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPfeiffer, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPollmanns, Claas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRippl, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchreiter, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchreiter, Miriam, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSpo